chick_weight <- ChickWeight %>% janitor::clean_names()

chick_weight %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = time,
             y = weight,
             group = chick,
             colour = diet)) +
  geom_line()

Use facet_wrap to get 4 separate charts, based on diet types

chick_weight %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = time,
             y = weight,
             group = chick,
             colour = diet)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ diet)

chick_weight %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = time,
             y = weight,
             group = chick,
             colour = diet)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ diet,
             nrow = 1)
